The course introduces the basic processes of the mind (input, representation, storing, integration and using of information) that underlie behavior. We will look at the most important regularities behind human behavior and variability of the behavior depending on age, gender, personality, ability and states of the individual. The course consists of (e-)lectures and seminars, reading material, different tasks and a final exam.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide a structured  introduction to the basic processes and regularities of human behaviour and its variability.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After this course a student: 1) Is able to see the basic processes (input, representation, storing, integration and using of information) of the mind as a necessary systems to guide behavior; 2) Knows how the basic processes of the mind function; 3) Knows how behavior varies depending on situations and individuals 4) Is able to analyze human behaviour
